{
  "stem": "1343.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- [SIGHS] And this went on until 1948.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When the state of Israel was established, it gave us a new life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We felt, even though the Arabs [LAUGHS] or the Israeli Jews don't like to hear it, from the ashes of the 6 million, Israel was established.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then, somehow, we accepted the fact that there is some justice in this world.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That something came out from this horrible tragedy of the humankind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After 2,000 years, we have a land, a country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And had there been one in the '30s, in the early '40s, who knows how many more Jews would be alive today.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We sent our belongings to Israel, bec-- frankly, not because we wanted so much to go, but because it was so hopeless to wait for America, it seemed, at one time.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But after, again, because we became complacent, that, oh, we suffered enough, we want to live [LAUGHS] a little-- I should say that one of my brother in-laws went to Palestine in '46, '47.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he kept on writing us to the camp-- don't come here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Life is very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But when it seemed, after four years, that we can't make it, we sent our belongings.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And yet, we stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So-- but after the establishment of the state of Israel, even though we did not go to Israel we felt that something is worthwhile to continue to live.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If, for nothing else, to help Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And again--",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
